Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity
O(log n)

At each recursive call, the exponent is divided by 2.

Space Complexity
O(log n)

Due to the recursion call stack.

Key Takeaway

Binary Exponentiation computes powers efficiently by recursively calculating x^(n/2) and reusing the result. This reduces the complexity from O(n) to O(log n), making it suitable for very large exponents.
